Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Form used/assessment name
Analysis pipeline identifier for version results
ABC-CT Study: T4 Follow-Up, Confirmation; Pediatric Feasibility
T4 Follow-Up Study termination point
Notes: 1=Withdrew consent at Main Study; 2=Lost to follow-up (Unable to contact prior to Screening contact); 3=Successfully re-contacted, but declined participation (Screener not completed); 4=Screened (Completed screener, but did not consent); 5 = Discontinued (Completed screener and consent but did not complete additional measures); 6=Virtual clinical measures only (Completed parent packet and/or Vineland and/or ADI-R); 7=T4D1 (Completed T4D1, but did not return for T4D2, or amidst Parent Packet); 8=T4D2 (Completed all T4 assessments, no show or other reason during the D2 visit)

ElementDescription: T4 Follow-Up Study termination reason
Notes: 1=All data provided (To be used for families who completed all T4 assessments); 2=Declined participation, completed Screener (To be used for families who are re-contacted and have completed the screener, but decide not to participant and consent.  The reason will be coded in the screener.); 3= Declined participation, did not complete Screener (To be used for families who were successfully re-contacted, but declined to participate before initiating Screener); 4=Consent Withdrawn (To be used only for families who withdrew consent during the main study and families who withdraw consent during T4); 5=Failed to come to T4D1 (To be used for families who complete screener, consent, and virtual assessments (parent packet, Vineland, ADI-R) and did not come in person for T4D1); 6=Failed to come to T4D2 (To be used for families who complete T4D1 in person visit but do not return for T4D2); 7=Other; 8=Unable to contact prior to Screening (Choice if Study Termination Point = 2=Lost to follow up (Unable to contact prior to Screening contact); 9=Discontinued (Completed screener and consent but did not complete additional measures)

ElementDescription: T4 Follow-Up Study termination reason Other description
Confirmation Study exit point
Notes: 1=Prior to CT1 data collection; 2=CT1 Data Collection; 3=CT2 Data Collection; 4=CT3 Data Collection

ElementDescription: Confirmation Study exit reason
Notes: 1=CS Screener Passed: Consent not fully executed; 2=CS Screener Passed: Consent Withdrawn; 3=CS Screener passed: Failed to come to Timepoint 1; 4=CS Screener passed: Other (not specified above); 5=CS Ineligible due to diagnostic disqualification at CT1(ADI-R, ADOS2/BOSA, DSM-5, and/or CASI-5); 6=CS Ineligible due to IQ-disqualification at CT1 (DAS-II); 7=CS Did not provide any valid biomarker (ET/EEG) data at CT1; 8=CS Lost to Follow Up; 9=CS Study measures/participation completed; 10=CS Other (not specified above)

ElementDescription: Confirmation Study exit reason other description
